            <i><strong> years;</strong> and he died.</i> <i> </i> 15 <i>And <strong>Mahalaleel lived sixty and five
                years, and
                begat Jared</strong>.</i> 16 <i>And</i> <i> Mahalaleel lived after he begat Jared eight hundred and
                thirty
                years, and</i> <i> begat sons and daughters. </i> 17 <i>And <strong>all the days of Mahalaleel were
                eight</strong></i> <strong> hundred ninety and five years;</strong> <i>and he died</i>."</p>
        <p> Let's use a little math: 130 moons divided by 12 = 10.8 years; 105 moons divided by 12 = 8.75 years; 90
            moons
            divided by 12= 7.5 years; 70 moons divided by 12 = 5.8 years; and 65 moons divided by 12= 5.41 years. If
            what these
            "enlightened ones" say is true, then Adam, according to verse 3, had a son when he was almost eleven years
            old; Seth
            had his first born when he was less than nine (verse 6); Enos when he was less than eight (verse 9); Cainan
            when he
            was almost six years old, (verse 12); and <strong>Mahaleel had a son when he was just five and a half years
                old,</strong> according to verse 15. <strong>As we can see their hypothesis is absolutely illogical, and
                not
                scientific.</strong> It is evident that not everyone who claims to be a scientist or to use scientific
            methods,
            is saying the truth. True science and true religion have to coincide, because true science can only discover
            what
            God has created, and true religion can say only what God said. What some people forget is that when <strong>our
                first fathers were 500 years old, they were as strong as an actual 35 or 40 years old man.</strong>
            <strong>The
                saddest thing of all this is that "Christian leaders" exist who believe these nonsensical
                hypothesis.</strong>
            Sure enough, many years ago I was taken by surprise when my Sunday School teacher, <strong>who was a medical
                doctor</strong> said: "With the knowledge I have of the human body I can assure you that nobody can live
            that
            long". Immediately he went to the blackboard and started to divide the total age of each patriarch by
            twelve, to
            "demonstrate" that the "so called" years were really "months" or "moons". When I went to the blackboard and
            divided
            by twelve the age at which those patriarchs had their first son, the only argument that came to his mind was
            to say:
            "Well, in different eras they counted time in different ways". Then I replied: "We are talking about the
            same
            passage, the same verse, and even the same man, not of different eras". <strong>It is very common that the
                hypertrophic ego of many brothers preclude them from rectifying in private, much less in
                public.</strong> This
            man was a Christian, he was not trying to harm the faith. His problem was that he had stuffed his mind with
            lots of
            pseudo scientific hypothesis. Sadly with the authority he had by virtue of being a medical doctor and a
            Sunday
            School teacher, he was unwillingly harming the faith of his brethren, who knew he was a scientist and an
            honest man.
            Sure enough, <strong>he was honest, but was honestly wrong,</strong> and <strong>the teachings of those
                brothers who
                are honestly wrong, are the worst of all.</strong> <a href="biblenotes.html">Back to Bible Notes
                Index</a></p>

